                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="62166" author="rhenwood" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 01:03:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The revision section of the manual needs updating to reflect on the continuous release and explain the use of version specific style elements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6947&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/6947&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59055" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 22 May 2013 14:12:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;another patch closes up this issue for at least another release:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5753&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,5753&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54282" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 17:41:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only l23 (lustre 2.3 and beyond) and l24 (lustre 2.4 an beyond) are currently configured. l21, l22, l25 should also be added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="54265" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 18 Mar 2013 16:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;landed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="49985" author="rhenwood" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 20:49:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since patch set 13 on:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4611&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#change,4611&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can see the lustre version specific conditional annotations in the html, xhtml, pdf and epub builds.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48020" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 16:45:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Not anything to see yet, I haven&apos;t hooked the custom transform into the make file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You need to checkout the change and run the command shown locally. Provided you&apos;re on a fedora 17 machine, it should work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="48019" author="rhenwood" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 16:43:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Draft for review.&lt;/p&gt;

